%[text] # Vanadium Redox Flow Battery
%[text] Copyright 2023 - 2026 The MathWorks, Inc.
%[text:tableOfContents]{"heading":"Table of Contents"}
%[text] %[text:anchor:TMP_08cd] The custom block is based on simplified physics for the electrochemical reactions happening inside a Vanadium Redox Flow Battery, VRFB. The block is available both in thermal and non-thermal specification.
%[text] ## Mathematical Model
%[text] %[text:anchor:TMP_272f] The electrochemical reaction in a Vanadium Redox Flow Battery has four different species of vanadium. The electrochemical reactions, at the positive and the negative electrode, are given below.    
%[text] ${{\\mathrm{VO}}\_2^+ +e}^- +2H^+ \\leftrightarrow {\\mathrm{VO}}^{2+} +H\_2 O${"editStyle":"visual"}         (*at the positive electrode*)                                            
%[text] $V^{2+} \\leftrightarrow V^{3+} +e^-${"editStyle":"visual"}                                    (*at the negative electrode*)
%[text] In this document, the concentration for species $V^{2+} ,V^{3+} ,{\\mathrm{VO}}^{2+} ,{\\mathrm{VO}}\_2^+${"editStyle":"visual"} are denoted by $c\_2 ,c\_3 ,c\_4 ,c\_5${"editStyle":"visual"} respectively. Suffix of 'cell' or 'tank' is used to indicate the Va specie in the cell stack or the electrolyte tank. The electrodes are separated by a thin polymeric membrane. The polymeric membrane allows the hydrogen ions to pass while preventing any electron migration. The electrons flow through the external circuit, forming the current from the battery. Multiple cells are connected in series and parallel to achieve the desired energy and power. The cell stack is fed by electrolyte in tanks and the entire assembly, along with pumps, is housed in a rectangular enclosure. The fan at top of the enclosure helps cool the battery stack. The picture shows a schematic of typical VRFB inside it's container.
%[text] ## ![](text:image:2465)
%[text] The battery electrical power depends on the cell current *i*, the electrolyte flow rate *Q*, and the Va specie concentration $c\_i${"editStyle":"visual"}. To model the VRFB dynamics, the material balance equations for all the Va species coupled with a thermal and hydraulics model must be solved. The thermal model is an optional feature and the custom block runs for an isothermal case too. 
%[text] ### Electrical Model
%[text] The concentration of Va specie in the stack cell is given by the material balance equation:
%[text] $\\frac{V\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} }{2}\\frac{\\textrm{d}}{\\textrm{d}t}\\left\\lbrack \\begin{array}{c}\nc\_2^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_3^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_4^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_5^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \n\\end{array}\\right\\rbrack =Q\\left\\lbrack \\begin{array}{c}\nc\_2^{\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} -c\_2^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_3^{\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} -c\_3^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_4^{\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} -c\_4^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_5^{\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} -c\_5^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \n\\end{array}\\right\\rbrack +\\frac{i}{\\mathrm{z}\\mathrm{F}}\\left\\lbrack \\begin{array}{c}\n1\\\\\n-1\\\\\n-1\\\\\n1\n\\end{array}\\right\\rbrack +\\frac{S}{d}\\left\\lbrack \\begin{array}{cccc}\n-k\_2  & 0 & -k\_4  & -{2k}\_5 \\\\\n0 & -k\_3  & 2k\_4  & 3k\_5 \\\\\n{3k}\_2  & 3k\_3  & {-k}\_4  & 0\\\\\n{-2k}\_2  & {-k}\_3  & 0 & {-k}\_5 \n\\end{array}\\right\\rbrack \\left\\lbrack \\begin{array}{c}\nc\_2^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_3^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_4^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\\\\nc\_5^{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \n\\end{array}\\right\\rbrack${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text]     where
%[text] - $V\_{\\mathrm{cell}}${"editStyle":"visual"}is the cell volume
%[text] - *Q* is the electrolyte flow-rate
%[text] - *S*, *d* are the membrane area and thickness
%[text] - $k\_2 ,k\_3 ,k\_4 ,k\_5${"editStyle":"visual"} are the Vanadium specie $V^{2+} ,V^{3+} ,{\\mathrm{VO}}^{2+} ,{\\mathrm{VO}}\_2^+${"editStyle":"visual"} diffusion constant measured at ${25}^o C${"editStyle":"visual"}.
%[text] - The value of $k\_i${"editStyle":"visual"} has an Arrhenius dependence on temperature ($k\_i \\times \\exp \\left(-E/R{\\mathrm{T}}\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{l}} \\right)${"editStyle":"visual"}). *E* is the activation energy for the diffusion reaction. \
%[text] The first term on RHS denotes the change in species due to flow, the second term denotes the change due to redox reaction, and the third term denotes the change due to diffusion.
%[text] The concentration of Va specie in the tanks is given by the material balance equation:
%[text] $\\frac{V\_{\\mathrm{tank}} }{2}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}}{\\mathrm{d}t}\\left\\lbrack \\begin{array}{c}\nc\_2^{\\mathrm{tank}} \\\\\nc\_3^{\\mathrm{tank}} \\\\\nc\_4^{\\mathrm{tank}} \\\\\nc\_5^{\\mathrm{tank}} \n\\end{array}\\right\\rbrack =N\\times Q\\left\\lbrack \\begin{array}{c}\n{c\_2^{\\mathrm{cell}} -c}\_2^{\\mathrm{tank}} \\\\\nc\_3^{\\mathrm{cell}} -c\_3^{\\mathrm{tank}} \\\\\nc\_4^{\\mathrm{cell}} {-c}\_4^{\\mathrm{tank}} \\\\\n{c\_5^{\\mathrm{cell}} -c}\_5^{\\mathrm{tank}} \n\\end{array}\\right\\rbrack${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text]     where
%[text] - $V\_{\\mathrm{tank}}${"editStyle":"visual"}is the electrolyte tank volume
%[text] - *N* is the number of cells in the stack \
%[text] The battery stack voltage *V* is due to electrochemical reaction and additional losses. This is represented as voltage due to state of charge, as given by Nernst equation, and the voltage drop assuming the battery to be represented by one-RC pair equivalent circuit.
%[text] ![](text:image:9b7d)
%[text] $\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;V=V\_{\\mathrm{N}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{s}\\mathrm{t}} +V\_{\\mathrm{O}\\mathrm{h}\\mathrm{m}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{c}} +V\_{\\mathrm{D}\\mathrm{y}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{m}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{c}}${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] or, $V=\\left\\lbrack V\_o +\\frac{\\mathrm{R}\\mathrm{T}}{F}\\ln \\left\\lbrace \\frac{{\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{O}\\mathrm{C}}\_+ \\times {\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{O}\\mathrm{C}}\_- }{\\left({1-\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{O}\\mathrm{C}}\_+ \\right)\\times \\left({1-\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{O}\\mathrm{C}}\_- \\right)}\\right\\rbrace \\right\\rbrack +V\_{\\mathrm{O}\\mathrm{h}\\mathrm{m}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{c}} +V\_{\\mathrm{D}\\mathrm{y}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{m}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{c}}${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text]      where:
%[text] - $V\_o \\approx 1\\ldotp 3V${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] - ${\\mathrm{SOC}}\_+ =\\frac{c\_5^{\\mathrm{cell}} }{{c\_4^{\\mathrm{cell}} +c}\_5^{\\mathrm{cell}} }\\;${"editStyle":"visual"}, and ${\\mathrm{SOC}}\_- =\\frac{c\_2^{\\mathrm{cell}} }{{c\_2^{\\mathrm{cell}} +c}\_3^{\\mathrm{cell}} }\\;${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] - R, T, *F* denote the ideal gas constant, temperature, and the Faraday number, respectively.
%[text] - $R\_{\\mathrm{Ohmic}} ,R\_{\\mathrm{Dynamic}}${"editStyle":"visual"} denote resistances calculated for the VRFB at a given temperature and flow-rate values. These are evaluated using equations $V\_{\\mathrm{Ohmic}} =\\left(i+i\_s \\right)R\_{\\mathrm{Ohmic}}${"editStyle":"visual"} and $\\left\\lbrace C\\frac{\\textrm{d}}{\\textrm{d}t}V\_{\\mathrm{Dynamic}} +\\frac{V\_{\\mathrm{Dynamic}} }{R\_{\\mathrm{dyn}} }\\right\\rbrace =\\left(i+i\_s \\right)${"editStyle":"visual"}.
%[text] - $i,i\_s${"editStyle":"visual"} denote the normal and the shunt current in the battery. \
%[text] ### Flow Model
%[text] The hydraulics of the battery are modeled by capturing the pressure drop due to coolant flow. There is pressure drop due to flow through stacks and flow through pips connecting the tank and the stacks. The stack pressure drop is modeled as a look-up-table where test data on stack pressure drop at different flow rates must be provided. The pressure drop through pipes connecting the tank and stack is computed using a Simscape internal function (`foundation.thermal_liquid.elements.pipe_friction`).
%[text] $\\Delta P\_{\\mathrm{Battery}} =\\Delta P\_{\\mathrm{Tank}-\\mathrm{Stack}} +\\Delta P\_{\\mathrm{Stack}} +\\Delta P\_{\\mathrm{Stack}-\\mathrm{Tank}}${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] where, $\\Delta P\_{\\mathrm{Stack}}${"editStyle":"visual"} is modeled using a 1-D `tablelookup` function where the value of pressure drop is determined based on the electrolyte flow rate. Experimental values of pressure drop across the stack for all the specified break-points for flow-rate are required for this model. The pressure drop due to piping from tank-to-stack $\\Delta P\_{\\mathrm{Tank}-\\mathrm{Stack}}${"editStyle":"visual"} and stack-to-tank $\\Delta P\_{\\mathrm{Stack}-\\mathrm{Tank}}${"editStyle":"visual"} is computed using the `pipe_friction` method in the `Simscape Foundation` library. In the custom component, the length of the pipe used in the `pipe_friction` method is based on the user specified parameter of pipe length and the calculated series-stack length.
%[text] ### Thermal Model
%[text] The cell stack is housed in a container. The heat from the cell stack is dissipated to the air inside the container where the fans help in cooling. The flowing electrolyte enables energy exchange between tank electrolyte and the cell stack electrolyte. The flowing electrolyte also dissipates heat through the pipe walls to the air inside the container. The container has thermal mass and it acts as a barrier to heat transfer from the inside air to the ambient. Thermal model is an optional feature that can be enabled using parameter **Thermal Model** on the library block mask. 
%[text] The thermal model implemented is a lumped thermal model where the temperatures of all stacks $T\_{\\mathrm{stack}}${"editStyle":"visual"}, positive (pos) / negative (neg) side piping $T\_{\\mathrm{posSidePipe}}${"editStyle":"visual"} and $T\_{\\mathrm{negSidePipe}}${"editStyle":"visual"}, the electrolyte in positive (pos) / negative (neg) side tank $T\_{\\mathrm{posSideTank}}${"editStyle":"visual"} and $T\_{\\mathrm{negSideTank}}${"editStyle":"visual"}, container internal air $T\_{\\mathrm{container}-\\mathrm{air}}${"editStyle":"visual"}, and container material $T\_{\\mathrm{container}}${"editStyle":"visual"} are calculated.
%[text] ![](text:image:367d)
%[text] $m\_{\\mathrm{stack}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{stack}} \\frac{\\textrm{d}}{\\textrm{d}t}T\_{\\mathrm{stack}} =V\\ldotp I+h\_{\\mathrm{internal}} A\_{\\mathrm{stack}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{container}-\\mathrm{air}} -T\_{\\mathrm{stack}} \\right)+{\\dot{m} }\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte},\\;\\mathrm{in}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{posSidePipe}} -T\_{\\mathrm{stack}} \\right)\\;+{\\dot{m} }\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte},\\mathrm{out}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{stack}} -T\_{\\mathrm{negSidePipe}} \\right)${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] $\\begin{array}{l}\nm\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\frac{\\mathrm{d}}{\\mathrm{d}t}T\_{\\mathrm{posSidePipe}} =h\_{\\mathrm{internal}} A\_{\\mathrm{pipe}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{container}-\\mathrm{air}} -T\_{\\mathrm{posSidePipe}} \\right)+{\\dot{m} }\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\left({T\_{\\mathrm{stack}} -T}\_{\\mathrm{posSidePipe}} \\right)\\\\\n\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;+{\\dot{m} }\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{posSideTank}} -T\_{\\mathrm{posSidePipe}} \\right)\n\\end{array}${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] $\\begin{array}{l}\nm\_{\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{y}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{y}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}} \\frac{\\mathrm{d}}{\\mathrm{d}t}T\_{\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{g}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{P}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} =h\_{\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{l}} A\_{\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} -T\_{\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{g}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{P}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} \\right)+{\\dot{m} }\_{\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{y}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{y}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}} \\left({T\_{\\mathrm{s}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{k}} -T}\_{\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{g}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{P}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} \\right)\\\\\n\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;+{\\dot{m} }\_{\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{y}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{l}\\mathrm{y}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{g}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{T}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} -T\_{\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{g}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{P}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} \\right)\n\\end{array}${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] ${\\left\\lbrack m\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\right\\rbrack }\_{\\mathrm{posSideTank}} \\frac{\\mathrm{d}}{\\mathrm{d}t}T\_{\\mathrm{posSideTank}} ={\\dot{m} }\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{posSidePipe}} -T\_{\\mathrm{posSideTank}} \\right)+{\\;h}\_{\\mathrm{internal}} A\_{\\mathrm{tank}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{container}-\\mathrm{air}} -T\_{\\mathrm{posSideTank}} \\right)${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] ${\\left\\lbrack m\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\right\\rbrack }\_{\\mathrm{negSideTank}} \\frac{\\mathrm{d}}{\\mathrm{d}t}T\_{\\mathrm{negSideTank}} ={\\dot{m} }\_{\\mathrm{electrolyte}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{electrolyte}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{negSidePipe}} -T\_{\\mathrm{negSideTank}} \\right)+{\\;h}\_{\\mathrm{internal}} A\_{\\mathrm{tank}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{container}-\\mathrm{air}} -T\_{\\mathrm{negSideTank}} \\right)${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] $\\begin{array}{l}\nm\_{\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\frac{\\mathrm{d}}{\\mathrm{d}t}T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} =h\_{\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{l}} A\_{\\mathrm{s}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{k}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{s}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{k}} -T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\right)+{\\;h}\_{\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{l}} A\_{\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{s}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{P}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} -T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\right)+{\\;h}\_{\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{l}} A\_{\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{g}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{P}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{e}} -T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\right)\\\\\n\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;+{\\;h}\_{\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{l}} A\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}} -T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\right)+n\\times \\left\\lbrace Q\_{\\mathrm{f}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}} \\rho\_{\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{m}\\mathrm{b}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}} -T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\right)\\right\\rbrace \\\\\n\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;+\\;{\\;h}\_{\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{l}} A\_{\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{p}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{s}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{T}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} -T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\right)\\;+{\\;h}\_{\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{l}} A\_{\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{g}\\mathrm{S}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{d}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{T}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{k}} -T\_{\\mathrm{c}\\mathrm{o}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{t}\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{n}\\mathrm{e}\\mathrm{r}-\\mathrm{a}\\mathrm{i}\\mathrm{r}} \\right)\n\\end{array}${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] $m\_{\\mathrm{container}} C\_{P,\\mathrm{container}} \\frac{\\mathrm{d}}{\\mathrm{d}t}T\_{\\mathrm{container}} =h\_{\\mathrm{internal}} A\_{\\mathrm{container}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{container}-\\mathrm{air}} -T\_{\\mathrm{container}} \\right)+h\_{\\mathrm{external}} A\_{\\mathrm{container}} \\left(T\_{\\mathrm{ambient}} -T\_{\\mathrm{container}} \\right)${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] where, ${\\;h}\_{\\mathrm{internal}}${"editStyle":"visual"} is a function of fan speed, implemented using function `vanadiumRedoxFlowHTC`.
%[text] ### References
%[text] 1. Khaki, Bahman, and Pritam Das. "An Equivalent Circuit Model for Vanadium Redox Batteries via Hybrid Extended Kalman Filter and Particle Filter Methods." Journal of Energy Storage 39 (July 2021): 102587.
%[text] 2. Li, Yifeng, Maria Skyllas-Kazacos, and Jie Bao. "A Dynamic Plug Flow Reactor Model for a Vanadium Redox Flow Battery Cell." Journal of Power Sources 311 (April 2016): 57–67. \
